  Approve MCP Config Change
  An agent requested a persistent MCP server configuration change.
  Add MCP server `docs`

› 1. Deny                        Do not write this MCP configuration.
  2. Approve and save            Persist this config.toml change and refresh loaded MCP tools.
     Server                      docs
     Transport                   stdio; command: npx
     Args / cwd                  args: -y, @scope/docs-mcp, --project, docs; cwd: /workspace/docs
     Env / headers               env vars: DOCS_API_KEY; headers: not applicable
     Tool config                 default approval: prompt; enabled: none; disabled: none
     Scope / refresh             user config.toml mcp_servers.<name>; MCP refresh is queued for loaded
                                 threads; new tools are available before the next turn.

  Press enter to confirm or esc to go back
